.","pos":[14645,14745]},{"content":"Performs a graceful shutdown of the domain.","pos":[14784,14827]},{"content":"The application domain is not unloaded until all threads running in the domain have either stopped or are no longer in the domain.","pos":[14828,14958]},{"pos":[14967,15139],"content":"[!NOTE]\n The common language runtime does not support serialization of global methods, so delegates cannot be used to execute global methods in other application domains.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"The common language runtime does not support serialization of global methods, so delegates cannot be used to execute global methods in other application domains.","pos":[9,170]}]},{"content":"The unmanaged interfaces described in the common language runtime Hosting Interfaces Specification also provide access to application domains.","pos":[15146,15288]},{"content":"Runtime hosts can use interfaces from unmanaged code to create and gain access to the application domains within a process.","pos":[15289,15412]},{"pos":[15421,15472],"content":"The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment variable","linkify":"The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment variable","nodes":[{"content":"The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment variable","pos":[0,51]}]},{"content":"An environment variable that sets the default loader optimization policy of an executable application.","pos":[15475,15577]},{"pos":[15587,15593],"content":"Syntax","linkify":"Syntax","nodes":[{"content":"Syntax","pos":[0,6]}]},{"pos":[15651,15658],"content":"Remarks","linkify":"Remarks","nodes":[{"content":"Remarks","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"A typical application loads several assemblies into an application domain before the code they contain can be executed.","pos":[15661,15780]},{"content":"The way the assembly is loaded determines whether its just-in-time (JIT) compiled code can be shared by multiple application domains in the process.","pos":[15787,15935]},{"content":"If an assembly is loaded domain-neutral, all application domains that share the same security grant set can share the same JIT-compiled code.","pos":[15945,16086]},{"content":"This reduces the memory required by the application.","pos":[16087,16139]},{"content":"If an assembly is not loaded domain-neutral, it must be JIT-compiled in every application domain in which it is loaded and the loader must not share internal resources across application domains.","pos":[16149,16344]},{"content":"When set to 1, the COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment flag forces the runtime host to load all assemblies in non-domain-neutral way known as SingleDomain.","pos":[16351,16509]},{"content":"SingleDomain loads no assemblies as domain-neutral, except Mscorlib, which is always loaded domain-neutral.","pos":[16510,16617]},{"content":"This setting is called single domain because it is commonly used when the host is running only a single application in the process.","pos":[16618,16749]},{"pos":[16757,16959],"content":"[!CAUTION]\n The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment flag was designed to be used in diagnostic and test scenarios. Having the flag turned on can cause severe slow-down and increase in memory usage.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment flag was designed to be used in diagnostic and test scenarios. Having the flag turned on can cause severe slow-down and increase in memory usage.","pos":[12,200],"nodes":[{"content":"The COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization environment flag was designed to be used in diagnostic and test scenarios.","pos":[0,105]},{"content":"Having the flag turned on can cause severe slow-down and increase in memory usage.","pos":[106,188]}]}]},{"pos":[16969,16981],"content":"Code example","linkify":"Code example","nodes":[{"content":"Code example","pos":[0,12]}]},{"pos":[16984,17241],"content":"To force all assemblies not to be loaded as domain-neutral for the IISADMIN service can be achieved by appending <ph id=\"ph1\">`COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization=1`</ph> to the Environment’s Multi-String Value in the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\services\\IISADMIN key.","source":"To force all assemblies not to be loaded as domain-neutral for the IISADMIN service can be achieved by appending `COMPLUS_LoaderOptimization=1` to the Environment’s Multi-String Value in the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\services\\IISADMIN key."},{"pos":[17429,17437],"content":"See also","linkify":"See also","nodes":[{"content":"See also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[17560,17623],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Programming with Application Domains and Assemblies<ept id=\"p1\">](index.md)</ept>","source":"[Programming with Application Domains and Assemblies](index.md)"},{"pos":[17626,17661],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Using Application Domains<ept id=\"p1\">](use.md)</ept>","source":"[Using Application Domains](use.md)"}]}